### **Position Summary**

The company **PONTICELLI NIGERIA** , a subsidiary of the Ponticelli Frères Group, is recruiting as part of its projects to lead and oversee large\-scale industrial construction projects in the Oil \& Gas sector.


Would you like to develop your experience as a **Tender Manager (M/F)** and help transform the world as part of a family\-owned group that works to provide people with what they will always need: energy, health, water, food and security, while sincerely respecting the planet and its employees?




We invite you to join us on a **project\-based contract** . The position is based in **Port Harcourt, Nigeria.**

Playing a key role in delivering profitable project opportunities, with regard to PNL projects, the Tender Manager (M/F) will be responsible for costing, preparing budgets, preparing bids and providing clarifications until the award. The Tender Manager will be familiar with the general specifications and requirements of Oil\&Gas EPC and Offshore projects.


He will always be mindful of, and never compromise, our Health, Safety and Quality values and procedures.


The position we are offering involves the following main responsibilities:


* examine tender documentation, including operational provisions, technical specifications, and commercial requirements;
* liaise with suppliers, partners and all internal departments involved in the tendering process and define respective deliverables;
* define/propose technical solutions, methodologies, execution strategy and draft work schedules;
* perform cost calculations and project budgeting;
* prepare and submit the technical and commercial proposals, according to client requirements and company’s guidelines;
* liaise and attend meetings with the client throughout the entire bid cycle;
* produce reports and maintain complete records throughout the bidding process to ensure approval, traceability, and ultimately efficient handover to project teams;
* be involve in business development activities from time to time e.g. social media marketing activities, or conference and trade show attendance;
* manage relationships with Customers, on the tender clarification stages;
* manage the tender strategy to meet Customer requirements;
* prepare, Issue and follow\-up tenders, pricing/cost spreadsheet and clarification with related documentation management and filing/archiving;
* proper distribution/collection of documents during Preparation/ review/Negotiation of Tenders;
* ensure that per each tender, a Peer Review is properly carried out;
* liaising with Technical, Contract and Procurement Dept. for advice on :
	+ method statement and technical solutions;
	+ services/Subcontractors’ selection and management until the finalisation of the agreement;
* liaise with Planning \& Risk Manager for Tender Risks.

### **Profile Wanted**

You have a mechanical engineer degree or similar degree is requested.




You have a minimum of 5 years in a similar role as tender, bid or proposal engineer in an Oil\&Gas EPC company.




You have an excellent communication skills, and you are fluent in English.




If you would like to join us in supporting global change, we look forward to hearing from you!



L'entreprise en quelques mots

Ponticelli Nigeria \[PNL] is a subsidiary of the Ponticelli Group, a leading European services supplier to companies in the energy, industrial, and infrastructural sectors.


PNL specializes in world\-class construction and upgrade services for Oil and Gas facilities in the Nigerian market, both onshore and offshore.


We design, build, modernize, and maintain production installations to ensure long\-term safety and performance.


PNL has executed projects for major companies such as TotalEnergies E\&P Nig. Ltd., Chevron Nig. Ltd., Nigerian Agip Oil Company, and ExxonMobil.


Our commitment to improvement has allowed us to maintain a leadership position in the Nigerian Oil \& Gas Market.”

### **Position Summary**

MAIN MISSION: Lead all activities related to the Electrical, Instrumentation, and Telecom (EIT) scope for an onshore project, from construction engineering to construction and commissioning on site.  



Technical Coordination and Project Management


* Monitor procurement activities related to EIT;
* Accountable for EIT material traceability with MTracker;
* Manage potential subcontractors;
* Ensure compliance with deadlines, costs, and quality of technical deliverables;

Construction Engineering


* Verify Detailed Engineering consistency and quality;
* Issuance of Technical Queries;
* Review E\&I Method Statement from E\&I Subcontractor;
* Supervise the Subcontractor Team regarding technical preparation of works;
* Implement, manage, and lead the Job Cards system preparation for the EIT scope with Job Cards done by the subcontractor;
* Accountable for Construction Engineering progress;
* Provide input to Planning;
* Participate in Construction Engineering coordination;

Construction Activities


* Manage resources, planning, and progress while reporting to the Project Construction Manager;
* Ensure compliance with HSE standards, quality procedures, and technical specifications;

Commissioning Engineering


* Oversee the EIT commissioning engineering activity;
* System and subsystem review (provide inputs if necessary);
* Commissioning procedures review;
* Attend meetings with COMPANY and COM Engineering Subcontractor;
* Oversee and manage the EIT subcontractors and commissioning activity at site;
* Follow commissioning execution schedule (provide input to Planning Level 4\);
* Review and approve EIT commissioning check sheets.

### **Profile Wanted**

\- Construction Manager / Commissioning Manager / Project \- Manager experience in EIT (10 years);


* Proven experience in Oil \& Gas projects;
* Skills in project management, technical coordination, and team leadership;
* Proficiency in site project control tools (Job Cards, planning, reporting);
* Proficiency in English required;
* Familiarity with ICAPS software;
* Availability for mobilization to Nigeria – PHC from November 2025 to May 2026\.


L'entreprise en quelques mots

Founded in 1986, TCPI is a Portuguese company and part of the Ponticelli Group. Its area of expertise covers electricity, instrumentation and automation throughout the entire lifecycle of installations, including engineering, construction and industrial maintenance. TCPI's teams operate in a wide range of sectors, including oil, gas and energy. They are craftsmen of industry, creating and maintaining complex infrastructures throughout the world. With subsidiaries in France, Belgium, Angola, Cameroon and Mozambique, TCPI is a key player in the development of industrial infrastructures.

