Founded in 2007 (originally as Beta Shipping), Tetra Maritime is a Nigerian ship owner and operator specializing in tailored marine logistics across the upstream, midstream, and downstream oil & gas supply chain. With a fleet of Nigerian-flagged vessels operating across the African continent, and a strategic partnership with Union Maritime, a UK-based ship owner with global acclaim, we are committed to delivering end-to-end logistics solutions to our clients.

We are seeking a highly organised and detail-oriented Junior Compliance professionals with experience in some or all of the following, to support the Group’s global governance, compliance, and corporate administration activities:

corporate administration;
corporate governance and entity management;
corporate restructuring;
regulatory filings & deadline management;
KYC and compliance;
company secretarial support.

Key Responsibilities

Support statutory filings and corporate registry submissions across multiple jurisdictions (UK, Singapore, Bermuda, India, etc.) and prepare required corporate documentation;
Assist with entity management and corporate administration for a global SPV portfolio;
Draft board minutes, written resolutions, and maintain statutory registers and corporate records;
Conduct KYC/AML onboarding and compliance checks on third parties;
Prepare and provide KYC documentation and group structure charts to banks, counterparties, and service providers;
Coordinate cross‑border incorporations, dissolutions, and corporate changes;
Support intragroup restructurings;
Maintain departmental trackers, databases, and filing systems;
Liaise with banks, auditors, legal counsel, and corporate service providers;
Provide general administrative, compliance, and CoSec support to the legal team.

Requirements

At least 1 year’s experience in a legal, compliance, corporate services, or financial services environment (experience in shipping, commodities, finance, or SPVheavy groups is an advantage).
Exposure to some or all of the following:
company secretarial;
statutory filings & corporate registry submission
corporate authorities & board documentation
KYC and compliance;
crossborder corporate changes and restructurings
interaction with ship registries or overseas registries (advantageous)
Joint ventures and other corporate matters.

Key attributes:

strong drafting and document preparation skills
high level of organization and attention to detail
ability to work with energy, agility, and resilience across multiple fast‑moving matters
excellent interpersonal skills and confidence liaising with internal teams and external stakeholders
strong project‑management mindset and ability to track multiple deadlines
reliable document management and record‑keeping skills;

Tetra Maritime is a leading global shipowner with an ever-increasing range of activity and relationships, which results in a growing need for strategic, high-impact communication. This new role will play a pivotal role in shaping and amplifying our voice—internally and externally—ensuring that our narrative aligns with our ambitions. This role is central to building trust, engagement, and clarity across our global team and with our external stakeholders.

Role Definition: Senior Legal Officer

We are seeking a high-class Legal Counsel to join our global team, with experience in some or all of the following:

• ship sale and purchase;

• asset finance;

• corporate finance;

• JVs and other corporate transactions;

• regulatory work and government/agency engagement.

Requirements

The ideal candidate will have 5+ years’ PQE at a leading corporate and/or law firm, in Nigeria (i.e. top tier national or multinational) or internationally (but now resident in Lagos), with either shipping expertise, or highclass experience from commodities, oil and gas, finance, aviation, or similar. The candidate should have a focus on non-contentious work including some or all the following:

• Asset sale and purchase;

• Bank facilities;

• Share issue, sale and purchase;

• Joint ventures.

Key Attributes

• First class drafting;

• · Energy, agility and resilience for work embedded with commercial colleagues on numerous fast- moving matters;

• · Strong inter-personal and project management skills: Legal works with numerous other functions and externals;

• · Good legal sector connections.

